ok dug into the code a little more... I think it's ok the continue with CID and update how the function below is determing values like the `agentURIType` and `feedbackURIType`

```
export function determineUriType(uri: string): string {
  if (uri.startsWith("ipfs://")) {
    return "ipfs"
  } else if (isIpfsGatewayUrl(uri)) {
    return "ipfs"  // Gateway URLs are still IPFS
  } else if (isIpfsCid(uri)) {
    return "ipfs"
  } else if (uri.startsWith("https://")) {
    return "https"
  } else if (uri.startsWith("http://")) {
    return "http"
  } else {
    return "unknown"
  }
}
```

you could add a URIType enum to make that explicit but also I don't think it's necissarily needed 

Looking at the examples queries here - https://sdk.ag0.xyz/4-subgraph/4-3-example-queries/ - I am not seeing a query pattern folks will need that is something like "fetch me on all the agents with arweave data"  which might be more tricky with this approach

The alternative would probably be something like a storageType enum and that is added to the schema but this would require a migration and reindexinig of the data.

TLDR I think it's ok to ship as is with updates to that function to ensure the type is set correctly so I'll work on that and share it back. I don't think it would be a big lift to change it, the lift would be on the migration and reindexing
